				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well sssaid, brother.  Iksar have the greatessst potential for roleplaying.  I think ten of my twelve Sssocials are ressserved for that purpossse.  I rarely ssspeak in the game, except if I really know sssomeone, I am sssent a /tell, or resssponding to a /shout.<BR>
<BR>
Zirulan, I sssee your hissss is as pronounced as mine, but might I recommend not hissssing on Z or SH sssounds, and only once per word?  It doesss get dissstracting to even me and I do it as often as I ssspeak.<BR>
<BR>
Now for sssome really tasssty tidbitsss for you role-playersss out there.  Find sssome really great animationsss and cussstomize them.  All of thessse are taken from an Iksar model and might look a little weird on other racesss, but they do well for examplesss: <BR>
<BR>
/cough looksss like an Iksar pulling his head back and quickly biting air in front of him.  I Hotkeyed &quot;/cough say snaps sharply at %T!&quot;<BR>
: Everglade snaps sharply at Daniel!<BR>
<BR>
/yawn opens the Iksarsss mouth and he coversss it with his left hand.  I Hotkeyed &quot;/yawn say catches a bug and eats it!&quot;<BR>
: Everglade catches a bug and eats it!<BR>
<BR>
/cheer makes the Iksar open his mouth while tilting his head back and slowly at firssst, he thrusssts his handsss into the air, ringing his fisssts.  I made two Hotkeysss for thisss, both are war criesss that I use right before engaging in combat.  &quot;/cheer say shouts, 'For the Legion of Cabilis!'&quot;<BR>
: Everglade shouts, 'For the Legion of Cabilis!' <BR>
NOTE:  Thisss is an e-mote, not a real shout.<BR>
The other was a two part Sssocial.  &quot;/shout say gets ready to strike....&quot; + &quot;/e warns, 'There shall be no tolerance for your kind!&quot;<BR>
: Everglade gets ready to strike....<BR>
: Everglade warns, 'There shall be no tolerance for your kind!'<BR>
<BR>
I use /nod as it is, but there are no good preprogrammed e-motesss for 'no' ssso I made &quot;/veto say shakes his head at %T.&quot;<BR>
: Everglade shakes his head a Tug.<BR>
<BR>
/cringe makes the Iksar cowl away and put handsss over his face.  I sssplit thisss in two to make it easier to sssee in the heat of combat.  &quot;/cringe say is taking a beating.&quot; + &quot;/e needs healing.&quot;<BR>
: Everglade is taking a beating.<BR>
: Everglade needs healing.<BR>
<BR>
/peer causesss the Iksar to ssslowly look down and up again.  I Hotkeyed &quot;/peer say looks %T up and down.  Mmm, %S looks delicious!&quot;  It works great to freak out newbiesss, as an alternate to overusing the war criesss, and is a good way to ressspond to people who asssk you what'sss going on? when you'd rather not ssspeak.<BR>
: Everglade looks Daniel up and down.  Mmm, he looks delicious!<BR>
: Everglade looks Tattiana up and down.  Mmm, she looks delicious!<BR>
: Everglade looks a giant spider up and down.  Mmm, it looks delicious!<BR>
It is great fun when they reciprocate with /shiver or /gasp.  If they use one of the /rude e-motes or /roar, I follow up by sssnapping sharply at them.  When used in combat, sssay against the ssspider, /drool or /bite makesss a good encore.<BR>
<BR>
/bleed ssswings an Iksar'sss head down and around ssso while I used to have &quot;/bleed say growls.&quot; it was jussst too easy to type in and I used it often in combat and while sssitting where the animation doesss not alwaysss show ssso I type that in now and replaced the Hotkey with &quot;/bleed say hisses and snarls.&quot;<BR>
: Everglade hisses and snarls.<BR>
<BR>
I didn't like the wording to /roar.  It was too wordy and kind of took the edge off.  Ssso I made &quot;/amaze say roars fiercely!&quot; which I use mossst often during combat, particularly when my Ssscreaming Mace yaulpsss.  Thisss makesss the Iksar ssstand up ssstraight with his shouldersss forward and throwsss his head back with his maw gaping.<BR>
: Everglade roars fiercely!<BR>
<BR>
Another two parter, but when used at the right time, it looksss sssuper cool.  If used too late, you look rather dumb.  &quot;point say bores his claws into %T's chest.&quot; + &quot;/e rips out %T's still beating heart!&quot;<BR>
: Everglade bores his claws into a gnoll commander's chest.<BR>
: Everglade rips out a gnoll commander's still beating heart!<BR>
NOTE: If thisss is used too early, the foe will keep fighting very long after you pull out it'sss heart.  If you use it too late, it'll look more like thisss....<BR>
: Everglade rips out Target's still beating heart!<BR>
NOTE:  If you are ssstoked about your kill, or really upssset at your latessst victim, and you have an audience, you can target the victim'sss corpssse and ssstill pull out his heart as normal.  It'll jussst be beating a little longer after he'sss dead, but the wording makesss up for that.  Alssso, D-ucking over the corpssse makes for better animation than pointing.  And no, &quot;corpse&quot; doesss not show up in the e-mote.<BR>
<BR>
When I sssit to ressst, I often type in &quot;/e chants lowly.&quot; or &quot;/calm&quot;.  With thisss and my pulling bugsss out of the air and eating them, roaring fiercely, growling, sssnarling, pulling out heartsss, biting, and calling out war criesss, I think I have truly caught the feel of an Iksar Monk -- particularly sssince I left Kunark at the fifth rite and my kind isn't very common in the landsss I've travelled to sssince.<BR>
<BR>
Yesss, I know people often complain about thossse who insssist on being perpetually in-character, but without ssspeaking much, and showing them -- not jussst by using e-motesss but actually showing them with animationsss -- no-one has yet complained and even thossse with little tolerance have joined in.  You can alwaysss tell the ametuersss.  They are the onesss who use nothing but /rude and /roar, but hey, it is sssomething.  The bessst I sssaw was when a Red /con /cringed from my when I looked her up and down....<BR>
<BR>
It looksss sssomewhat funny on your ssscreen but it looksss normal to everyone elssse.  I will sssee &quot;You emote, 'roars fiercely!'&quot; but when you are used to being behind the veil in roleplaying gamesss, you perform for your audience more than you do for yourssself.  I had enough sssatisfaction when I drove sssomeone nutsss trying to figure out how I was eating fliesss and another perssson thought with all the new thingsss that came out in Kunark, we Iksar were given new e-motesss.<BR>
<BR>
Pick any of your favorite animationsss from the essstablished e-motesss and if you've been paying attention ssso far, you'll know by now you jussst type &quot;say&quot; and whatever you want to show up after your name inssstead of the regular text.<BR>
<BR>
Remeber SPORT (you don't need to be an English major) to persssonalize the Sssocial to the current target.<BR>
%S is the Sssubject and usesss He, She, It.<BR>
%P is Possssesive and sssays His, Hersss, or Its.<BR>
%O is Objective to disssplay Him, Her, It.<BR>
%R is Race.  Thisss won't disssplay non-playable racesss, and will inssstead sssay Race, but I'm sure the Player vs. Player ssservers will have sssome fun with &quot;/raise say says, 'Barbarians (%r) have no place in our realm!'&quot;<BR>
%T is the Target'sss name.<BR>
<BR>
Actually, it is ssso much sssimpler to use %T in normal ssspeech, ssso if you want to warn that a Sssand Giant is near the dock, you may as well &quot;/shout %T at dock!&quot; inssstead of &quot;/shout SG at dock!&quot; and have all the newbiesss wondering what SG is while they are getting butchered becuassse they didn't run sssoon enough.  And &quot;%T near wood bridge,&quot; is much better than &quot;Griff near wood bridge,&quot; becaussse it is shorter and letsss everyone know if it's a Griffawn, Griffin, or Grim Feather.  Becaussse we are all interesssted in making thisss more roleplay friendly if we're reading thisss, it alssso helpsss cut down on the obsssolete anacronymsss which you sssee way, way too many of and sssounds more like what a perssson would actually shout in each sssituation.<BR>
<BR>
Anywaysss, if you are in Lanys T'Vyl, come sssee me and check out my e-motesss firssst hand.  I'd like to sssee what you come up with for your race.  If you aren't in Lanys T'Vyl, feel free to use the onesss I've exampled here, but again, they will look sssilly on non Iksar.  Their behaviour and animationsss are different.  Magiciansss and Necromancersss already have many commandsss Hotkeyed for their ssservants ssso along with &quot;/pet attack&quot; you may as well add the line &quot;/point say orders, 'Bring me %P's head!'&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Necromancersss might try thisss:<BR>
/pet attack<BR>
/pet target<BR>
/point say demands, 'Carve 'im in your image, %T'<BR>
/assist<BR>
<BR>
This should order your ssskeleton to claw away at your foe, tell your pet to kill it disssplaying the pet'sss name, and automatically help him out.<BR>
<BR>
Get creative.  Not everyone is againssst roleplaying.  A great deal of them jussst don't realize all the neat thingsss they can do and they won't catch on if they don't sssee usss doing it.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
